comments: LaVine (CHI) and Herro (MIA) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball on the perimeter.
Adebayo (MIA) brings his off-arm toward Vucevic's (CHI) side and marginal contact occurs as Adebayo attempts to dribble around Vucevic.
Vucevic (CHI) initiates contact with Adebayo's (MIA) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Martin (MIA) is moving laterally and does not establish a legal guarding position prior to the illegal contact with DeRozan's (CHI) body, which affects his SQBR during the drive to the basket.
Beverley (CHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Martin (MIA) does not intentionally redirect the ball after the made basket.
Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in Butler's (MIA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Butler (MIA) rests his arm on DeRozan's (CHI) side and marginal contact occurs as he moves alongside him during the drive.
Butler (MIA) reaches for the ball and avoids contact with LaVine's (CHI) arm during the drive.
Adebayo (MIA) legally contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) does not take a controlled dribble before picking up the inbounds pass to start his drive.

Replay review of the foul called on Caruso (CHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Caruso (CHI) jumps toward and makes contact with Strus' (MIA) body after the release of the jump shot, which affects his ability to follow-through.
Martin (MIA) moves alongside of LaVine (CHI) with a resting arm on his body and marginal contact occurs before Adebayo (MIA) cleanly blocks the driving shot attempt.
White (CHI) initiates contact with Adebayo's (MIA) arm on his way to the ball, which affects Adebayo's SQBR and ability to maintain control of the ball.
Strus (MIA) and Caruso (CHI) engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Caruso (CHI) commits a take foul on Butler (MIA).
LaVine (CHI) does not bring his hand underneath the ball as he switches directions before passing.
LaVine (CHI) slips by Herro (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as Herro briefly engages and immediately disengages during the pick.
Herro (MIA) legally contests White's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
